# Android IME — Cursor Rules

## Architecture
`InputMethodService` + Canvas-drawn view. No deprecated `android.inputmethodservice.Keyboard`.

## Class Responsibilities

### ClaviIME.kt
- Owns all state: `currentLanguage`, `shifted`, `capsLock`, `translitMode`, `symbolsMode`, `diacriticsLocale`
- `handleCharacter(key)`: commit text → diacritics check → if space, run TextFixEngine
- `handleBackspace()`: clear diacritics + fix suggestion, delete char or pop translit buffer
- `flushTranslitBuffer(force)`: resolve digraph buffer → commitText
- Reads SharedPreferences in `onCreateInputView()` only

### ClaviKeyboardView.kt
- All drawing in `onDraw()`: strip then keys
- `onTouchEvent()`: dispatch to strip or key area
- Properties: `clipItems`, `diacriticItems`, `fixSuggestion`
- Interfaces: `OnKeyListener`, `OnStripListener`

### TranslitEngine.kt
- `tryTransliterate(buffer): Pair<String, Int>?` — returns (cyrillic, charsConsumed) or null
- `isDigraphStart(c): Boolean` — true for `s`,`z`,`k`,`t`,`c`,`i`,`y`
- KMU 2010 rules: shch(4)→щ, zh/kh/ts/ch/sh/iu/ia/ie/yi(2)→ Ukrainian

### TextFixEngine.kt
- `analyze(textBefore: String): Fix?`
- Fix types in order: double space → space-before-punct → missing-space-after-sent → ukr typos → en typos → repeated chars
- `Fix(original, fixed, description)` — original/fixed are FULL textBefore strings, not just the changed word

### DiacriticsEngine.kt
- `suggest(char, locale): List<String>` — frequency-ordered, includes base letter as last
- Returns empty list if no variants (diacritics strip hidden)
- Supports: pt, de, no, nb, fr, es, sv, fi, pl

## Patterns to Follow
```kotlin
// Reading prefs — only in onCreateInputView, not on every keypress
val prefs = getSharedPreferences(SettingsActivity.PREFS_NAME, MODE_PRIVATE)

// Committing text
currentInputConnection?.commitText(text, 1)

// After fix applied — clear the suggestion
keyboardView.fixSuggestion = null

// Inside Paint.apply{} — use this.textSize to avoid val shadowing
val paint = Paint().apply { this.textSize = 14f * density }
```

## Common Pitfalls
- `val textSize` in outer scope + `textSize =` inside `apply {}` → Kotlin thinks you're reassigning the val. Use `this.textSize =`.
- `InputConnection` can be null between keystrokes — always null-check.
- `ClipboardHistory` must `stopListening()` in `onDestroy` — leak otherwise.
- `translitBuffer` must be cleared in `onFinishInputView` and `onStartInputView`.
